야외수영장은 공용수영장으로 썬베드를 설치하였습니다. 멀리 보이는 제제기오름을 바라보는 태닝과 물놀이는 더없는 여유를 드릴 것입니다.
심플하면서도 모던한 디자인을 지닌 객실입니다. 사진으로 표현하지 못한 감성을 느껴보시기 바랍니다.
이 공간의 숨은 공간입니다. 스파욕조가 있어 아이들을 씻기거나 연인이 오름을 바라보며 스파시설을 이용하는 낭만적인 공간입니다.
침실은 침대용파레트위에 더블매트를 올려놓았으며, 호텔침구로 세팅을 합니다. 혹시나 잠을 주무시다 떨어져도 안전합니다.
스파시설이 있는 공간입니다. 블라인드를 통해 때로는 은밀하게, 때로는 시원한 연출이 가능하며 별도의 공간이라 특히 여성분이나 아이들이 좋아하는 공간입니다.

거실겸 주방이미지입니다.
거실이 넓어 추가인원이 투숙하시게 되면 요와이불세트를 제공하고 있습니다.
특급호텔은 아니지만, 그래도 최소한의 편의를 제공하는것이 저희의 욕심입니다.
총 3가지의 타입으로 구성되어 있으며, 10객실로 이루어져 그 어떤 리조트나 호텔보다 프라이빗하고 조용하게 지낼 수 있습니다. 모든 공간에 테라스가 있습니다. 밤에 5월에 피는 감귤꽃향기, 9월이나 10월의 제주공기는 그 어떤 지역보다도 싱그러운것 같

모든 객실은 앞에서보면 2층으로 시작되지만 뒷공간 주차장과 이어진 객실은 1층으로 시작됩니다.
주차장에서 차를 세우시고 카페로 오시면 체크인안내를 도와드리겠습니다.
저희 숙소는 작은 공간에도 감성으로 채워놓기 위해 소소한 곳에도 신경을 쓰고 있습니다. 저희의 감성을 고스란히 전달해지길 원하고 있어요 ^^

Artist's tower on the sea.
The creation of the tower followed the protocol that was fashionable in Italy during and after the Renaissance. A scale model on wood plus the great help from old local artisans left behind from the tragedy of technology.
The light, one of the elements of magic, of Isla Colon Bocas del Toro, illuminates the tower in all it's splendid isolation.

Artist's tower on the sea.
The creation of the tower followed same protocol that was fashionable in Italy during and after the Renaissance. A scale model on wood plus the great help from old local artisans left behind from the tragedy of technology.

As the tower came to completion, the artist came to the realization that his "opera" had become a "pagoda on the sea" a fruit of his subconscious  entangled in the surroundings  around his childhood.The mementos of his father a diplomat in China... .
The front facing the land of "Bahia Saigon" sports a sculpture  with a flower pot behind with the caption "Medusae"one of the latest works by the artist owner: Filiberto Bonaventura.

The turret and top bed. 
The turret is at the very top, and is almost completely occupied by an "almost" double bed, ideal for lovers and with incredible views of mountains and sea.

The kitchen and dining area.
The kitchen boasts a very modern electric stove with a glass cover, and a gas oven underneath, also a lovely small table in the middle with space for six people, a hammock and various objects and paraphernalia... .

Harmoniously located in the middle of one of the most beautiful landscapes in the world and a world heritage site, the Patacancha basin in the Sacred Valley of the Incas, Cusco. Here you can sleep under millions of stars in rooms designed to provide a unique experience in contact with nature, cultural heritage in the ancestral community of Huilloc.

Glamping Eco Spirit invites you to this great space where you will be moved by the energy of the mountains of the sound of birds and wind brushing the trees. Experience the serenity that emanates from the water and the warmth of the fire that is born from adventure, passion and your trip.

Welcome to Murakami! Relax in a spacious traditional Japanese tatami room! This will be your private room during your stay :)
We have an entire building devoted to hosting our guests. You will be sharing the facilities in our guesthouse with 5 other rooms.

The booking includes 2 meals: a Japanese breakfast and a luxurious seafood course (Funamori) on the night of your arrival! If you would rather not have raw fish, we can prepare it cooked :) Also, if you prefer beef, there is also the Wakasa Beef meal plan for an extra 2,500JPY/person
Depending on the season, you will be able to try out all kinds of seafood.
Mr. Murakami can take you on a boat tour around the bay!
Mr. Murakami can take you out fishing on a dock. (You cannot fish off the boat, though).
Your host, Mr. Murakami will take you on a 1 hour boat tour around the coast to show you his beautiful hometown. You will not be able to fish from the boat, but you can enjoy the spectacular view.
This is your host, Mr & Mrs Murakami. They will take great care of you during your stay :)
There are multiple bathrooms located in different parts the building.
You can also use the washing machine to wash your clothes.
All of our toilets are modern and clean.
This is the changing area where you can put your clothes.
When this red banner is hung up, the bath is only available for women.
When it's the men's turn, you will see the blue banner.
There are also a few sinks in the changing area.
In Japan, it is customary to wash your body first by the showers and then enter the hot bath once you are clean.
The dining area is in a separate building. Both dinner and breakfast will take place here.
We provide air conditioners in each room with both heating and cooling functions.
Two vending machines are located at the entrance of the guesthouse where you can easily get soft drinks and alcoholic beverages.
There is a common area in the guesthouse, where you can talk with other guests and enjoy a game of Go.
As long as the weather permits, you will be able to enjoy 1 hour at sea with your host, Mr. Murakami.
This is the view of the Fishermen's village from the sea.
We provide basic amenities such as toothbrushes, hand soap, and hair dryer in each bathroom.
There is free parking for all guests staying at Murakami.
He will show you all the fishing spots around the bay. You cannot fish from the boat, but you can do dock and pier fishing.
Here are some guests enjoying fishing off of the dock!
Here are some guests who stayed with us enjoying the boat tour!
Locals collect seaweed and hang them under the sun to get dried seaweed.
When you have time, a stroll around the village will give you great insight on how the villagers here live. Their lifestyle has remained mostly unchanged for hundreds of years.
There is a stunning beach within 5 minutes walking distance from Murakami where you can go swimming!
One of the national treasures of Japan, Myotsuji Temple is well worth a visit if you are interested in learning about Buddhism and the history of Obama city.
A great spot to view to sunset right in the heart of Obama City. Mermaid Terrace is only 800m away from Obama Park and there are many temples and shrines along the way that you can stop by at.
